Package org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed

Class FreeIdScanner

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.id.indexed.FreeIdScanner
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable
    class FreeIdScanner
extends Object
implements Closeable
    Responsible for starting and managing scans of a GBPTree, populating a cache with free ids that gets discovered in the scan. Ids which are placed into cache are also marked as reserved, i.e. not free anymore. This way those ids that were found in one "round" of a scan will not be found in upcoming rounds and reserving ids becomes more of a batch operation.

      • ongoingScanRangeIndex

        private Long ongoingScanRangeIndex
        State for whether or not there's an ongoing scan, and if so where it should begin from. This is used in findSomeIdsToCache(LinkedChunkLongArray, int, PageCursorTracer) both to know where to initiate a scan from and to set it, if the cache got full before scan completed, or set it to null of the scan ended. The actual Seeker itself is local to the scan method.

      • tryLoadFreeIdsIntoCache

        boolean tryLoadFreeIdsIntoCache​(boolean awaitOngoing,
                                PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Do a batch of scanning, either start a new scan from the beginning if none is active, or continue where a previous scan paused. In this call free ids can be discovered and placed into the ID cache. IDs are marked as reserved before placed into cache.
